The Firma Advisory, a leading law and consulting firm in Nigeria, has announced its partnership with Access Partnership, the world’s leading public policy consultancy focused on technology. According to a press statement by Firma Advisory, the partnership is meant to “create a framework for future cooperation to enhance the effectiveness of policy in the technology sector”. The Partnership is also aimed at creating a collaboration that will drive positive change and foster technological advancements across the continent of Africa. The Firma Advisory statement also revealed that its partnership with Access Partnership will focus on areas such as thought leadership, policy development, stakeholder engagement, advocacy, and business development collaboration.